section.p:
Here is an example. The goal is to simplify the following fraction:
\frac{ \frac{1}{x + 1} - \frac{3}{x - 2}}{ \frac{2} {x - 2} + \frac{1}{x + 3}}
We will first do the calculation by adding the fractions in the numerator and denominator, and then dividing the resulting fractions by multiplying by the reciprocal.
\begin{aligned} \frac{\frac{1}{x + 1} - \frac{3}{x - 2}}{ \frac{2} {x - 2} + \frac{1}{x + 3}} \amp = \frac{ \frac{1 \cdot (x - 2)}{(x + 1) \cdot (x - 2)} - \frac{3 \cdot (x + 1)}{(x - 2) \cdot (x + 1)}}{ \frac{2 \cdot (x + 3)} {(x - 2) \cdot (x + 3)} + \frac{1 \cdot (x - 2)}{(x + 3) \cdot (x - 2)}} \amp \eqnspacer \amp \text{Common Denominator} \\ \amp = \frac{ \frac{(x - 2) - (3x + 3)}{(x + 1) (x - 2)} }{ \frac{(2x + 6) + (x - 2)} {(x - 2) (x + 3)}} \\ \amp = \frac{ \frac{-2x - 5}{(x + 1) (x - 2)} }{ \frac{3x + 4} {(x - 2) (x + 3)}} \amp \amp \text{Combine like terms} \\ \amp = \frac{-2x - 5}{(x + 1) (x - 2)} \cdot \frac{(x - 2) (x + 3)}{3x + 4} \amp \amp \text{Multiply by the reciprocal} \\ \amp = - \frac{(2x + 5)(x - 2)(x + 3)}{(x + 1)(x - 2)(3x + 4)} \amp \amp \text{Multiply and factor out the negative} \\ \amp = - \frac{(2x + 5)(x + 3) \cdot \cancel{(x - 2)}}{(x + 1)(3x + 4) \cdot \cancel{(x - 2)}} \amp \amp \text{Reduce} \\ \amp = - \frac{(2x + 5)(x + 3)}{(x + 1)(3x + 4)} \amp \amp \text{Reduce} \\ \end{aligned}

We will now do the same calculation, but we will multiply the numerator and denominator by the same value to
eliminate the fractions inside of the fraction. 

	\begin{aligned}
		\frac{\frac{1}{x + 1} - \frac{3}{x - 2}}{ \frac{2} {x - 2} + \frac{1}{x + 3}}
		\amp = \frac{\frac{1}{x + 1} - \frac{3}{x - 2}}{ \frac{2} {x - 2} + \frac{1}{x + 3}} \cdot \frac{(x+1)(x-2)(x+3)}{(x+1)(x-2)(x+3)} \amp \eqnspacer \amp \text{Multiply top and bottom} \\
		\amp = \frac{\frac{(x+1)(x-2)(x+3)}{x + 1} - \frac{3(x+1)(x-2)(x+3)}{x - 2}}{ \frac{2(x+1)(x-2)(x+3)} {x - 2} + \frac{(x+1)(x-2)(x+3)}{x + 3}} \amp \amp \text{Distribute} \\
		\amp = \frac{\frac{\cancel{(x+1)}(x-2)(x+3)}{\cancel{x + 1}} - \frac{3(x+1)\cancel{(x-2)}(x+3)}{\cancel{x - 2}}}{ \frac{2(x+1)\cancel{(x-2)}(x+3)} {\cancel{x - 2}} + \frac{(x+1)(x-2)\cancel{(x+3)}}{\cancel{x + 3}}} \amp \amp \text{Reduce} \\
		\amp = \frac{(x-2)(x+3) - 3(x+1)(x+3)}{2(x+1)(x+3) + (x+1)(x-2)} \amp \amp \text{Rewrite and simplify} \\
		\amp = \frac{(x^2 + x - 6) - (3x^2 + 12x + 9)}{(2x^2 + 8x + 6) + (x^2 - x - 2)} \\
		\amp = \frac{-2x^2 - 11 x - 15}{3x^2 + 7x + 4} \\
		\amp = - \frac{2x^2 + 11 x + 15}{3x^2 + 7x + 4} \amp \amp \text{Factor out the negative} \\
		\amp = - \frac{(2x + 5)(x + 3)}{(x+1)(3x + 4)} 
	\end{aligned}
